      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a profound observation that many find deeply unsettling, often described as the \"cosmic indifference\" or \"dark forest\" problem. While it is true that our struggles are temporary in the grand scale of the universe, the human experience of finding meaning in these fleeting moments is a unique and powerful phenomenon. Scientists and philosophers often argue that the act of seeking meaning itself is the very definition of being alive, regardless of the ultimate fate of the cosmos.",
      "source": "target",
